      <biogHist id="md5-fc67009d29c52bf4bedae6fa404147b4">
        <p>Librarian. 1925-.  Andre Nitecki came to the University in 1975 as associate professor of Library  and Information Studies, gaining his full professorship in 1981.  A specialist in library classification,  he has also taught African art at the Universities of Lagos, Ibadan and Ghana, and participated in  the Thai Royal Household Library Project.  He has been active in Canadian University Services  Overseas (CUSO) and assisted in organizing the Conference of Africanists, held at the University in  1986.</p>
      </biogHist>
